name: language-kumachan
readme:
# language-kumachan

A support package of the [KumaChan](https://notabug.org/mizusato/KumaChan) programming language for the Atom Editor. (Experimental)

Features:
- Syntax Highlighting
- Autocomplete
- Lint on Save
- <del>Rename (limitation: only available for local bindings)</del> (not working now)
- File Outline
- Quick Run

Key Bindings:
- <del>Rename: Shift+F6</del>
- Run File: Shift+F7 (limitation: only available for standalone scripts)

Note:
In order to enable "Autocomplete", "Lint on Save" and "Quick Run", the environment variable `KUMACHAN_PATH` should be set to the path of a directory containing a built KumaChan interpreter.

## Installation

Currently there is something wrong with atom.io/packages. The newest version of this package is required to be installed directly from GitHub:
```
$ apm install mizusato/language-kumachan
```
